[[Image:Vicencia 0445.jpg|thumb|Bust of Vicência Barbosa de Melo (ex-owner of the city)]] '''Vicência''' is a city in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. It is 81&nbsp;km away from the state capital [[Recife]]. It has an estimated ([[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|Ibge 2009]]) population of 27,877 inhabitants. [[File:Bandeira de Vicência.jpg|thumb|right|160px|City Flag]]
==Geography== [[Image:Baoba Poco Comprido.JPG|thumb|rIGHT|240px|Typical [[Baobab]] tree, often saw in [[Pernambuco]]]]
* State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Zona da Mata (coastal)|Zona da mata Pernambucana]] * Boundaries - [[Timbaúba]] and [[Macaparana]] ('''N'''); [[Limoeiro]] and [[Buenos Aires, Pernambuco|Buenos Aires]] ('''S'''); [[Aliança]] ('''E'''); [[Bom Jardim, Pernambuco|Bom Jardim]] and [[São Vicente Ferrer, Pernambuco|São Vicente Ferrer]] ('''W''') * Area - 230.82&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 119 m * Hidrography - [[Goiana River]] * Vegetation - [[Subcaducifólia]] forest * Clima - Hot tropical and humid * Annual average temperature - 25.3 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 81&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Vicência''' are based in food & beverage industry and [[agribusiness]], especially [[sugarcane]], [[banana]]s; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]] and [[poultry]].
